s-buffett-gates-rich-list-trillion-combined-net-worth-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%2C%20Jeff%20Bezos%2C%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20Warren%20Buffett%2C%20and%20two%20other%20centibillionaires%20are%20worth%20nearly%20%241%20trillion%20between%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jwilkins%40insider.com%20(Joseph%20Wilkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A231%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fmusk-bezos-buffett-gates-rich-list-trillion-combined-net-worth-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20The%20Importance%20Of%20Banning%20Polygamy%20In%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20Law%20Commission's%20call%20for%20public%20input%20on%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20(UCC)%20and%20the%20subsequent%20mention%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20a%20considerable%20amount%20of%20commentary%20has%20been%20generated%20on%20the%20topic.%20Some%20have%20endorsed%20the%20UCC%20citing%20equality%20and%20gender%20justice.%20Others%20have%20criticized%20it%20saying%20it%20won't%20take%20into%20account%20the%20country's%20diverse%20socio-cultural%20realities.%20In%20this%20column%2C%20we%20delve%20into%20the%20contentious%20matter%20of%20polygamy%2C%20a%20practice%20that%20is%20problematic.%20Polygamy%2C%20a%20custom%20entrenched%20in%20certain%20cultural%20and%20religious%20practices%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20serious%20repercussions%20in%20terms%20of%20gender%20equity%20and%20justice.%C2%A0A%20retired%20High%20Court%20Judge-led%20Panel%20in%20Assam%20has%20recently%20recommended%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftinyurl.com%2F6ekub72v%5C%22%3EAssam%20government%20to%20ban%20polygamy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Subsequently%2C%20%C2%A0the%20media%20reports%20suggest%20that%20Assam%20is%20planning%20to%20bring%20in%20a%20law%20banning%20polygamy%20this%20financial%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20polygamy%20has%20been%20prevalent%20in%20India.%20The%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201955%2C%20outlawed%20this%20practice%20for%20Hindus.%20Ditto%20for%20Sikhs%2C%20Jains%2C%20and%20Buddhists%20through%20their%20respective%20personal%20laws.%20It%20is%20also%20forbidden%20under%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%2C%20which%20enables%20inter-religious%20marriages.%20However%2C%20polygamy%20is%20permissible%20for%20Muslims%20under%20the%20Shariat%20Protection%20Act.%20Also%2C%20polygynous%20marriages%20are%20common%20in%20many%20tribal%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20there%20have%20been%20cases%20of%20people%20converting%20to%20Islam%20to%20remarry%20without%20the%20legal%20dissolution%20of%20their%20first%20marriage.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20declared%20such%20conversions%20solely%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20a%20second%20marriage%20as%20invalid%20in%20the%201994%20Sarla%20Mudgal%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20was%20reiterated%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Lily%20Thomas%20v.%20Union%20of%20India.%20These%20judgements%20have%20aimed%20to%20prevent%20the%20misuse%20of%20religious%20freedom%20to%20circumvent%20laws%20against%20polygamy%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20the%20legal%20dissolution%20of%20the%20first%20marriage%20is%20necessary%20prior%20to%20conversion%20and%20remarriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20approach%20presents%20complex%20social%20and%20legal%20challenges.%20It%20is%20the%20second%20wife%20and%20children%20born%20from%20such%20marriages%20that%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20this%20injustice.%20It%20becomes%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20exercise%20their%20rights%20to%20maintenance%20and%20inheritance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20such%20conversions%20for%20remarriage%20tend%20to%20create%20legal%20ambiguities%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20social%20and%20familial%20strife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202023%2C%20however%2C%20a%20bench%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justices%20PS%20Narasimha%20and%20JB%20Pardiwala%20was%20requested%20by%20Ashwini%20Upadhyay%20to%20hear%20cases%20on%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20polygamy%20and%20nikah%20halala.%20To%20which%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20responded%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20consider%20it.%20At%20an%20appropriate%20stage%2C%20I%20will%20constitute%20a%20Constitution%20bench%26quot%3B.%20The%20court's%20decision%20to%20reexamine%20the%20validity%20of%20polygamy%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20part%20of%20its%20broader%20commitment%20to%20promoting%20gender%20equality%20and%20protecting%20the%20rights%20of%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolygamy%20has%20been%20subject%20to%20feminist%20criticism%20due%20to%20its%20implications%20for%20gender%20inequality%20and%20the%20subjugation%20of%20women.%20Feminist%20scholars%20argue%20that%20polygamy%20perpetuates%20patriarchal%20power%20structures.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20also%20reinforces%20the%20unequal%20treatment%20of%20women%20within%20marriage%20and%20the%20family.%20Some%20scholars%20contend%20that%20polygamy%20allows%20men%20to%20have%20multiple%20wives%2C%20while%20women%20are%20limited%20to%20one%20husband%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20power%20imbalance%20and%20the%20unequal%20distribution%20of%20resources.%20This%20power%20imbalance%20is%20exacerbated%20by%20societal%20norms.%20Such%20norms%20often%20burden%20women%20with%20more%20family%20responsibilities%20than%20men%2C%20even%20when%20they%20seek%20work%20outside%20the%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20from%20Emory%20University%20noted%20increased%20levels%20of%20violence%20toward%20women%20and%20children%20in%20polygamous%20relationships%2C%20and%20that%20abuse%20can%20come%20from%20both%20husbands%20and%20co-wives.%20As%20India%20strives%20for%20social%20harmony%20and%20unity%20amidst%20its%20diverse%20religious%20and%20cultural%20practices%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20promote%20practices%20that%20uphold%20the%20principles%20of%20equality%20and%20justice.%20Polygamy%2C%20particularly%20when%20it's%20associated%20with%20religious%20conversion%20solely%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20a%20second%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20need%20to%20highlight%20the%20economic%20dependency%20of%20women%20on%20their%20husbands%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20vulnerability%2C%20exploitation%2C%20and%20fear%20of%20divorce.%20The%20multiple%20wives%20often%20are%20solely%20economically%20dependent%20on%20their%20husbands.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20this%20limits%20their%20autonomy%20and%20agency%20within%20the%20marriage.%20This%20economic%20dependency%20perpetuates%20gender%20inequalities%20and%20restricts%20women's%20ability%20to%20make%20independent%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFeminist%20scholars%20argue%20that%20polygamy%20reinforces%20the%20notion%20of%20women%20as%20unequal%20to%20men%20and%20perpetuates%20the%20subjugation%20of%20women.%20Polygamy%20also%20disempowers%20women%20in%20their%20sexual%20relationships%20and%20reflects%20a%20culture%20of%20misogyny.%20It%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20form%20of%20male%20privilege%20and%20control%20over%20women's%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20being%20practised%20by%20some%20groups%2C%20polygamy%20is%20not%20widespread%20in%20India%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey-5.%20The%20prevalence%20of%20polygamy%20was%202.1%25%20among%20Christians%2C%201.9%25%20among%20Muslims%2C%201.3%25%20among%20Hindus%2C%20and%201.6%25%20among%20other%20religious%20groups.%20These%20low%20prevalence%20rates%20indicate%20a%20general%20societal%20move%20away%20from%20this%20practice%2C%20suggesting%20that%20a%20ban%20may%20be%20in%20line%20with%20evolving%20social%20attitudes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDrawing%20upon%20the%20philosophical%20frameworks%20provided%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20John%20Stuart%20Mill%20and%20Simone%20de%20Beauvoir%2C%20the%20discussion%20of%20individual%20liberty%20and%20equality%20highlights%20the%20troubling%20dimensions%20of%20polygamy.%20Mill%2C%20a%20staunch%20proponent%20of%20individual%20freedom%2C%20argued%20that%20such%20freedom%20is%20only%20limited%20when%20it%20begins%20to%20harm%20others%2C%20which%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20practice%20of%20polygamy%20that%20inherently%20generates%20harm%20through%20power%20imbalances%20and%20gender%20inequity.%20Simon%20de%20Beauvoir's%20feminist%20philosophy%20advocates%20the%20liberation%20of%20women%20from%20oppressive%20societal%20structures%2C%20clearly%20opposing%20systems%20like%20polygamy%20that%20diminish%20women's%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%2C%20psychological%2C%20and%20social%20ramifications%20of%20polygamy%20further%20underscore%20these%20inequities%2C%20creating%20a%20precarious%20and%20unjust%20situation%20for%20women.%20The%20views%20of%20contemporary%20scholars%2C%20the%20societal%20trend%20away%20from%20polygamy%2C%20and%20the%20potential%20negative%20impact%20all%20affirm%20the%20necessity%20of%20a%20ban.%20As%20we%20collectively%20strive%20for%20an%20equitable%20society%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20reassess%20practices%20such%20as%20polygamy%20that%20impede%20such%20progress%20and%20continue%20to%20subvert%20the%20principle%20of%20equal%20rights.%20Outlawing%20polygamy%20would%20not%20only%20uphold%20the%20societal%20march%20towards%20equality%20and%20justice%20but%20would%20also%20resonate%20with%20the%20philosophical%20underpinnings%20of%20freedom%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20respect%20for%20all%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bibek%20Debroy%20is%20the%20Chairman%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20(EAC-PM)%20%26amp%3B%20Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20Additional%20Private%20Secretary%20(Policy%20%26amp%3B%20Research)%2C%20EAC-PM.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20authors.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691409540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-09%2Fu9pd1cq8_marriage-generic-istock_625x300_11_September_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22http