iginID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fbanks-write-off-rs-14-56-trn-npas-in-last-nine-financial-years-centre-123080700464_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Net%20write-off%20loans%20by%20private%20sector%20banks%20stood%20at%20Rs%2073%2C803%20crore%20(RBI%20provisional%20data)%20in%20FY%202022-23%2C%20he%20said%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fbanks-write-off-rs-14-56-trn-npas-in-last-nine-financial-years-centre-123080700464_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fbanks-write-off-rs-14-56-trn-npas-in-last-nine-financial-years-centre-123080700464_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fbanks-write-off-rs-14-56-trn-npas-in-last-nine-financial-years-centre-123080700464_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20Manmohan%20Singh%3A%20How%20Prime%20Ministers%20Decided%20for%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07163001%2FFotoJet-12.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EVeteran%20journalist%20Neerja%20Chowdhury%20is%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20finest%20political%20reporters%20and%20commentators.%20An%20award-winning%20journalist%2C%20she%20has%20been%20covering%20political%20developments%20in%20the%20country%20for%20nearly%20five%20decades.%20She%20has%20provided%20eye-opening%20accounts%20of%20how%20some%20of%20the%20most%20important%20political%20decisions%20in%20independent%20India%20were%20taken%20by%20various%20prime%20ministers.%20Her%20first%20and%20latest%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EHow%20Prime%20Ministers%20Decide%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20based%20on%20her%20first-hand%20information%20or%20straight%20from%20the%20horse%E2%80%99s%20mouth.%20She%20covered%20the%20tenures%20of%20six%20prime%20ministers%2C%20namely%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20V.%20P.%20Singh%2C%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%2C%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%20from%201975%20to%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20prolific%20writer%2C%20she%20meticulously%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministers%20in%20a%20lucid%20way%20through%20the%20prism%20of%20six%20decisions%20of%20historic%20significance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20246px)%2085vw%2C%20246px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07163517%2F61fgCWwV1mL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22246%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07163517%2F61fgCWwV1mL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20642w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07163517%2F61fgCWwV1mL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-193x300.jpg%20193w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667004%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22383%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHow%20Prime%20Ministers%20Decide%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Neeraja%20Chowdhury.%20Publisher%3A%20Aleph%20Book%20Company.%20Photo%3A%20Amazon.in%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20as%20follows%3A%20the%20strategy%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20adopted%20in%20breaking%20the%20Janata%20Party%20in%201979%20and%20returning%20to%20power%20in%201980%2C%20after%20her%20humiliating%20defeat%20in%201977%3B%20the%20error%20of%20judgement%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20to%20undo%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EShah%20Bano%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%2C%20and%20his%20parleys%20with%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20leaders%20eventually%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20to%20come%20to%20power%3B%20V.P.%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20implementation%20of%20the%20Mandal%20Commission%20report%20to%20save%20his%20government%20which%20changed%20the%20face%20of%20contemporary%20politics%3B%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20decision%20that%20resulted%20in%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%3B%20the%20rapidly%20changing%20political%20scenarios%20that%20turned%20the%20avowed%20pacifist%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20into%20a%20nuclear%20hawk%20who%20greenlighted%20the%20testing%20of%20nuclear%20devices%3B%20and%20the%20mild%20professor%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20widely%20regarded%20as%20one%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20weakest%20prime%20ministers%2C%20who%20defied%20interest%20groups%20and%20foes%20within%20the%20political%20establishment%20to%20seal%20a%20historic%20nuclear%20deal%20with%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndira%20Gandhi%20and%20underhand%20dealings%20with%20the%20RSS%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%E2%80%99s%20first%20chapter%20starts%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%20with%20the%20title%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Secular%20Prime%20Minister%20Who%20Undermined%20Secularism%E2%80%9D.%20Chowdhury%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndira%20Gandhi%20was%20a%20Hindu%20first%20and%20a%20Hindu%20last.%E2%80%9D%20She%20writes%20that%20the%20RSS%20had%20made%20overtures%20to%20Gandhi%20all%20through%20the%20Emergency.%20RSS%20chief%20Balasaheb%20Deoras%20had%20written%20to%20her%20several%20times.%20Some%20RSS%20leaders%20had%20reached%20out%20to%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%20through%20Kapil%20Mohan.%20Now%2C%20in%201977%2C%20she%20would%20have%20to%20see%20how%20to%20respond.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20she%20would%20have%20to%20play%20this%20one%20very%20carefully%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chowdhury%20writes.%E2%80%9DJust%20as%20the%20RSS%20brass%20had%20reached%20out%20to%20her%20for%20help%2C%20she%20too%20used%20the%20RSS%20for%20her%20purposes%20%E2%80%93%20but%20carefully%20kept%20a%20distance%20between%20the%20organisation%20and%20herself.%20For%20all%20her%20opposition%20to%20the%20RSS%2C%20she%20had%20managed%20to%20get%20it%20to%20support%20the%20Emergency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhi%20was%20also%20described%20as%20a%20great%20usurper%20and%20a%20true%20proponent%20of%20Machiavellian%20politics%20who%20used%20not%20only%20her%20left-socialist%20friends%20in%20her%20own%20party%20to%20fight%20with%20the%20old%20syndicate%20in%201969%2C%20but%20opposition%20parties%20and%20RSS%20as%20well.%20The%20RSS%20was%20full%20of%20praise%20for%20her%20during%20the%20Bangladesh%20war%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20the%20division%20of%20Pakistan%20in%201971%2C%20and%20fully%20supported%20her%20on%20her%20comeback%20to%20power%20in%201980.%20The%20RSS%20also%20supported%20her%20during%20the%201983%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20state%20assembly%20elections%20and%20after%20her%20death%20in%201984%20to%20the%20Congress%20party%2C%20led%20by%20her%20son%20Rajiv%20Gandhi.%20In%20that%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20almost%20wiped%20out%20and%20got%20only%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%20Even%20the%20tallest%20leader%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20lost%20badly%20in%20Gwalior.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fhow-the-1971-bangladesh-liberation-war-helped-the-rss-regain-lost-ground%5C%22%3EWith%20the%20Creation%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20a%20Longstanding%20Dream%20of%20the%20RSS%20Was%20Achieved%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeerja%20Chowdhury%20provides%20insights%20into%20how%20Gandhi%20benefitted%20from%20the%20infighting%20within%20the%20Janata%20Party%20during%201977-79%2C%20and%20how%20she%20used%20her%20non-political%20contacts%20like%20Kapil%20Mohan%20of%20Mohan%20Mekins%20beverages%20(makers%20of%20Old%20Monk%20Rum%20and%20Golden%20Eagle%20Beer)%20and%20his%20nephew%20Anil%20Bali%20to%20woo%20rebel%20Raj%20Narain%20to%20break%20the%20Janata%20Party.%20She%20also%20writes%20about%20how%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%20used%20to%20meet%20Raj%20Narain%20at%20Kapil%20Mohan%E2%80%99s%20Pusa%20Road%20house%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20According%20to%20her%2C%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20close%20aide%20Anil%20Bali%20%E2%80%93%20whom%20she%20quoted%20in%20her%20book%20extensively%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CThe%20RSS%20helped%20Indira%20Gandhi%20come%20to%20power%20in%201980.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShe%20knew%20the%20RSS%20had%20supported%20her%20but%20she%20never%20acknowledged%20it%20publicly.%20She%20used%20to%20admit%20privately%20that%20had%20it%20not%20been%20for%20the%20support%20by%20the%20RSS%2C%20she%20could%20not%20have%20won%20353%20seats%2C%20one%20more%20than%20she%20had%20won%20in%20her%20heyday%20in%201971%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bali%20claims.%20He%20adds%20that%20%E2%80%9Cincreased%20temple%20going%20was%20not%20lost%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20RSS%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRSS%20chief%20Balasaheb%20Deoras%20had%20once%20remarked%20during%20the%20course%20of%20a%20conversation%2C%20%E2%80%98Indira%20Gandhi%20bahut%20badi%20Hindu%20hai%E2%80%99%20(Indira%20Gandhi%20is%20a%20staunch%20Hindu).%20Balasaheb%20Deoras%20and%20his%20brother%20saw%20in%20Indira%20Gandhi%20a%20potential%20leader%20of%20the%20Hindus%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bali%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20soon-to-be-launched%20book%2C%20published%20by%20Aleph%20Book%20Company%2C%20also%20says%20the%20RSS%20in%201971%20praised%20Indira%20Gandhi%20for%20hiving%20off%20Bangladesh%20and%20weakening%20Pakistan.%20But%20the%20book%20also%20claims%20that%20in%201980%2C%20BJP%20leader%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20was%20trying%20to%20secularise%20his%20image%20while%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20trying%20to%20Hinduise%20the%20face%20of%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20then%20RSS%20chief%20Madhav%20Sadashiv%20Golwalkar%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20Guruji%2C%20wrote%20to%20her%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20biggest%20measure%20of%20credit%20for%20this%20achievement%20goes%20to%20you.%E2%80%99%20In%201974%2C%20she%20won%20the%20RSS%E2%80%99s%20admiration%20again%20for%20exploding%20the%20nuclear%20device%20%E2%80%93%20the%20RSS%20had%20always%20advocated%20a%20militarily%20strong%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20coming%20back%20to%20power%20in%201980%2C%20she%20did%20sense%20unhappiness%20amongst%20Muslims%20about%20the%20Congress.%20However%2C%20she%20still%20wanted%20to%20%E2%80%9CHinduise%20her%20politics%E2%80%9D%20fully%20aware%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20silent%20nudge%20from%20the%20RSS%20or%20even%20a%20neutral%20stand%20by%20them%20towards%20her%20might%20help%20in%20her%20political%20journey%2C%20says%20Chowdhury%20in%20the%20book.%20And%20this%20was%20the%20reason%20she%20asked%20her%20son%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20to%20cultivate%20contacts%20and%20relations%20with%20RSS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CAlthough%20RSS%20had%20reached%20out%20to%20Indira%2C%20she%20refused%20to%20meet%20its%20leaders%20during%20the%20Emergency%20or%20in%20its%20immediate%20aftermath.%20But%20in%201982%2C%20halfway%20into%20her%20term%2C%20she%20asked%20Rajiv%20to%20meet%20Bhaurao%20Deoras%2C%20the%20brother%20of%20RSS%20chief%20Balasaheb%20Deoras%2C%20and%20open%20a%20dialogue%20with%20him.%20The%20meetings%20were%20fixed%20by%20Kapil%20Mohan.%20Bhaurao%20was%20then%20looking%20after%20the%20political%20wing%20of%20the%20RSS%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRajiv%20met%20Bhaurao%20thrice%20between%201982-84%2C%20when%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20still%20PM%2C%20and%20once%20in%20early%201991%2C%20when%20he%20was%20out%20of%20power.%20The%20first%20meeting%20was%20held%20in%20September%201982%20at%20the%2046%2C%20Pusa%20Road%20residence%20of%20Kapil%20Mohan.%20The%20second%20meeting%20also%20took%20place%20at%20Pusa%20Road%2C%20the%20third%20one%20was%20held%20at%20Anil%20Bali%E2%80%99s%20residence%20in%20Friends%20Colony.%20The%20fourth%20meeting%20was%20held%20at%2010%2C%20Janpath%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20he%20became%20prime%20minister%2C%20Rajiv%20did%20not%20meet%20Bhaurao.%20But%20they%20remained%20in%20touch.%20Halfway%20into%20his%20term%2C%20the%20RSS%20had%20made%20a%20request%20to%20Rajiv%20to%20facilitate%20the%20telecasting%20of%20the%20Ramayana%20serial%20by%20Ramanand%20Sagar%20on%20Doordarshan%20%E2%80%93%20it%20had%20run%20into%20hurdles.%20Congress%20leader%20H%20K%20L%20Bhagat%2C%20later%20to%20become%20minister%20for%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%2C%20was%20alarmed%20when%20Rajiv%20mentioned%20the%20RSS%20request%20to%20him%3B%20he%20warned%20Rajiv%20that%20it%20would%20open%20Pandora%E2%80%99s%20box%20%E2%80%93%20and%20generate%20a%20climate%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20BJP-VHP-RSS-led%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20movement%E2%80%A6%20Rajiv%20did%20not%20pay%20heed%20to%20Bhagat%E2%80%99s%20apprehensions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERajiv%20Gandhi%20and%20quid%20pro%20quo%20politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20book%20reveals%20several%20previously%20unknown%20details%20about%20what%20transpired%20behind%20the%20scenes%20that%20led%20to%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20bring%20a%20Bill%20to%20negate%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20in%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20case%2C%20one%20anecdote%20stands%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F14155953%2FShah_Bano.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-232306%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22475%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShah%20Bano.%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRajiv%2C%20if%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20convince%20me%20about%20this%20Muslim%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Bill%2C%20how%20are%20you%20going%20to%20convince%20the%20country%3F%E2%80%9D%20Sonia%20asked%20Rajiv%2C%20according%20to%20D.P.%20Tripathi%2C%20the%20late%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%20leader%20who%20was%20then%20a%20member%20of%20Rajiv%E2%80%99s%20inner%20circle.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20must%20stand%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20him.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20Sonia%20said%20in%20my%20presence%20(sic)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20book%20quotes%20Tripathi%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20undoing%20the%20Shah%20Bano%20judgement%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20through%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%20bill%20by%20parliament%20was%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20for%20a%20Ram%20Temple%20in%20Ayodhya.%20It%20was%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%20who%20opened%20the%20locks%20of%20Babri%20Masjid%20through%20a%20Faizabad%20court%20and%20televised%20it%20on%20national%20television%20Doordarshan%20on%20February%201%2C%201986.%20In%201989%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government%20who%20struck%20a%20deal%20with%20VHP%20to%20do%20%3Cem%3Eshilanyas%3C%2Fem%3E%20(foundation%20stone)%20at%20the%20disputed%20site%20in%20Ayodhya%20through%20his%20home%20minister%20Buta%20Singh%20and%20then%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20N.D.%20Tiwari.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EV.P.%20Singh%20and%20the%20new%20wave%20of%20political%20polarisation%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Indira%20and%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20the%20third%20chapter%20of%20the%20book%20is%20about%20V.P.%20Singh%20who%20became%20prime%20minister%20after%20the%20Congress%20party%20was%20routed%20in%20the%201989%20general%20elections.%20Although%20this%20chapter%20begins%20with%20how%20Singh%20was%20elected%20prime%20minister%20on%20December%201%2C%201989%2C%20through%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20parliamentary%20party%20meeting%20in%20the%20Central%20Hall%20of%20Parliament%20by%20maneuvers%2C%20deceit%2C%20and%20diplomacy%20of%20Arun%20Nehru%2C%20it%20also%20provides%20information%20about%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20politics%20after%20his%20exit%20from%20the%20Congress%20party%20and%20the%20subsequent%20formation%20of%20Janmorcha%20and%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20the%20National%20Front%2C%20and%20the%20formation%20of%20his%20short-lived%20government%20with%20the%20support%20of%20right-wing%20BJP%20and%20Left%20front%20communist%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20eight%20months%20of%20forming%20his%20government%2C%20Singh%20sacked%20deputy%20prime%20minister%20Devi%20Lal%2C%20signalling%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20end%20for%20his%20government.%20To%20counter%20Devi%20Lal%E2%80%99s%20politics%2C%20he%20suddenly%20announced%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Mandal%20Commission%20report%2C%20which%20recommended%2027%25%20of%20reservations%20in%20government%20jobs%20for%20the%20OBC%20and%20backward%20castes.%20This%20report%20was%20submitted%20to%20the%20President%20in%20December%201980%20but%20was%20in%20%E2%80%98cold%20storage%E2%80%99%20during%20the%20Congress%20governments%20throughout%20the%201980s%20following%20which%20VP%20Singh%20suddenly%20announced%20its%20implementation.%20This%20pandora%E2%80%99s%20box%20opened%20a%20new%20chapter%20in%20Indian%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20polarisation%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20and%20caste%2C%20upper%20castes%20versus%20backward%20castes%2C%20Mandal%20versus%20Kamandal%2C%20and%20Mandir%20versus%20Masjid%20%E2%80%93%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20BJP%20to%20emerge%20as%20a%20big%20political%20force%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENarasimha%20Rao%20and%20temple%20politics%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20chapter%20of%20the%20book%20is%20about%20P.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20and%20how%20he%20presided%20over%20the%20demolition%20of%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya.%20The%20book%20captures%2C%20in%20vivid%20detail%2C%20the%20sequence%20of%20events%20that%20led%20to%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20on%20December%206%2C%201992.%20It%20mentions%20a%20meeting%20journalist%20Nikhil%20Chakravartty%20had%20with%20Rao%20days%20after%20the%20demolition.%20The%20two%20had%20been%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F08155806%2FUntitled-design.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F08155806%2FUntitled-design.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F08155806%2FUntitled-design-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F08155806%2FUntitled-design-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-497197%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDemolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20on%20December%206%2C%201992.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20heard%20you%20were%20doing%20puja%20after%20twelve%20o%E2%80%99clock%20on%20December%206%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%99%20Chakravartty%20teased%20Rao.%20A%20stung%20Rao%20shot%20back%20at%20Chakravartty%2C%20%E2%80%9CDada%2C%20you%20think%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20politics.%20I%20was%20born%20in%20rajniti%20(politics)%20and%20I%20have%20only%20been%20doing%20politics%20till%20today.%20Jo%20hua%20voh%20theek%20hua%E2%80%A6.%20(What%20happened%2C%20happened%20for%20good.)%20Maine%20is%20liye%20hone%20diya%E2%80%A6ki%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20ki%20mandir%20ki%20rajniti%20hamesha%20ke%20liye%20khatam%20ho%20jaaye%20(I%20allowed%20it%20to%20happen%20because%20I%20wanted%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20temple%20politics%20to%20finish%20forever).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fbabri-masjid-the-timeline-of-a-demolition%5C%22%3EBabri%20Masjid%3A%20The%20Timeline%20of%20a%20Demolition%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20then%20media%20advisor%2C%20P.V.R.K.%20Prasad%2C%20the%20author%20says%20Rao%20instructed%20him%20to%20create%20a%20trust%20which%20could%20build%20a%20temple%20where%20the%20mosque%20had%20once%20stood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20Sunday%20after%20the%20demolition%20(December%2013%2C%201992)%2C%20Prasad%20had%20gone%20to%20see%20Rao.%20He%20had%20found%20the%20PM%20alone%20and%20in%20a%20reflective%20mood.%20%E2%80%98We%20can%20fight%20the%20BJP%2C%20but%20how%20can%20we%20fight%20Lord%20Ram%3F%E2%80%99%20he%20asked%20Prasad%20pensively.%20%E2%80%98When%20we%20say%20that%20the%20Congress%20is%20a%20secular%20party%2C%20it%20does%20not%20mean%20we%20are%20atheists%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20went%20on.%20%E2%80%98How%20far%20are%20they%20(BJP)%20justified%20in%20hoodwinking%20people%20by%20monopolising%20Lord%20Ram%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20constructing%20a%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAtal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%3A%20Pacifist%20to%20nuclear%20hawk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fifth%20chapter%20of%20the%20book%20is%20about%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20and%20how%20the%20once-avowed%20pacifist%20turned%20into%20a%20nuclear%20hawk%20by%20greenlighting%20the%20testing%20of%20nuclear%20devices%20in%20May%201998.%20According%20to%20the%20book%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20May%201998%2C%20India%20successfully%20conducted%20nuclear%20tests%20in%20Pokhran%2C%20a%20crowning%20glory%20of%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%E2%80%99s%20premiership.%20But%20way%20back%20in%201979%2C%20when%20he%20was%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20in%20the%20Morarji%20Desai%20cabinet%2C%20Vajpayee%20had%20opposed%20testing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManmohan%20Singh%20and%20the%20historic%20nuclear%20deal%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sixth%20and%20final%20chapter%20of%20the%20book%20is%20about%20the%20making%20of%20Dr.%20Manmohan%20Singh%20as%20prime%20minister%20in%20the%20year%202004%20and%20how%20the%20mild%20professor%2C%20widely%20regarded%20as%20one%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20weakest%20prime%20ministers%2C%20defied%20interest%20groups%20and%20foes%20within%20the%20political%20establishment%20to%20seal%20a%20historic%20nuclear%20deal%20with%20the%20United%20States.%20Remember%20Singh%20became%20prime%20minister%20with%20the%20support%20of%20Left%20parties%2C%20but%20he%20betrayed%20them%20to%20strike%20a%20nuclear%20deal%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F05%2FBush__Singh_in_New_Delhi.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22George%20W.%20Bush%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%202006%2C%20when%20they%20sighed%20the%20India-US%20Civil%20Nuclear%20Agreement.%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-139047%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGeorge%20W.%20Bush%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%202006%2C%20when%20they%20sighed%20the%20India-US%20Civil%20Nuclear%20Agreement.%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20reveals%20details%20about%20a%20meeting%20that%20was%20held%20at%2010%20Janpath%20in%20the%20afternoon%20on%20May%2017%2C%202004%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20Manmohan%20Singh%20to%20become%20PM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAccording%20to%20K.%20Natwar%20Singh%2C%20Sonia%2C%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%20were%20present%20in%20the%20room%20when%20he%20reached.%20She%20(Sonia)%20was%20sitting%20there%20on%20the%20sofa%E2%80%A6.%20Manmohan%20Singh%20and%20Priyanka%20(were%20there%20as%20well)%E2%80%A6%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20was%20looking%20distraught%E2%80%A6Then%20Rahul%20came%20in%20and%20said%20in%20front%20of%20all%20of%20us%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20will%20not%20let%20you%20become%20prime%20minister.%20My%20father%20was%20assassinated%2C%20my%20Dadi%20was%20assassinated.%20In%20six%20months%2C%20you%20will%20be%20killed.%20Rahul%20threatened%20to%20take%20an%20extreme%20step%20if%20Sonia%20did%20not%20listen%20to%20him.%20%E2%80%98This%20was%20no%20ordinary%20threat%2C%E2%80%99%20recalled%20Natwar%20Singh%2C%20%E2%80%98Rahul%20is%20a%20strong-willed%20person.%20He%20gave%20Sonia%2024%20hours%20to%20decide%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESonia%20was%20in%20tears%20after%20Rahul%20said%20he%20was%20prepared%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20any%20possible%20step%20to%20prevent%20his%20mother%E2%80%9D%20from%20taking%20up%20the%20prime%20ministership.%20And%20the%20rest%20is%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20being%20asked%20in%20various%20interviews%20why%20she%20has%20not%20covered%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20and%20his%20important%20decisions%20which%20influenced%20people%20and%20politics%2C%20Chowdhury%20says%20%E2%80%9Chis%20term%20is%20a%20work%20in%20progress%20as%20he%20works%20towards%20a%20third%20stint%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20epilogue%20of%20her%20book%2C%20she%20explained%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20decided%2C%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20fairness%20and%20accuracy%2C%20not%20to%20include%20the%20incumbent%20prime%20minister%20in%20this%20book.%20For%20one%2C%20his%20term%20is%20a%20work%20in%20progress%20and%20two%2C%20unlike%20with%20other%20prime%20ministers%2C%20what%20would%20have%20been%20missing%20with%20Modi%20would%20have%20been%20the%20power%20of%20hindsight%2C%20the%20journalist%E2%80%99s%20sole%20beacon%20to%20illuminate%20the%20inner%20working%20of%20a%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20and%20the%20PMO.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20confessed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20book%20will%20be%20incomplete%20without%20a%20word%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20fourteenth%20and%2C%20arguably%2C%20its%20most%20powerful%20prime%20minister%20seen%20in%20the%20context%20of%20his%20predecessors%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20book%20by%20Chowdhury%20illustrates%20how%20the%20power%20of%20the%20prime%20ministers%20played%20out%20under%20majority%20rule%20as%20well%20as%20in%20a%20coalition%20government.%20According%20to%20the%20author%2C%20her%20book%20is%20about%20power%20and%2