0of%20the%20Russian%20government%20via%20teleconference%20in%20Moscow%20on%20March%2010%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EMIKHAIL%20KLIMENTYEV%2FSPUTNIK%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESince%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20last%20year%2C%20companies%20have%20been%20scrambling%20to%20cut%20ties%20with%20Russia.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAn%20FT%20survey%20found%20that%20companies%20lost%20%E2%82%AC100%20billion%20attempting%20to%20leave%20the%20state.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Kremlin%20seized%20Danone's%20and%20Carlsberg's%20assets%20last%20month%2C%20Putin%20is%20determined%20to%20profit%20from%20outgoing%20firms.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEuropean%20companies%20have%20lost%20more%20than%20%E2%82%AC100%20billion%20in%20Russia%20since%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fc4ea72b4-4b02-4ee9-b34c-0fac4a4033f5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20February%20last%20year%2C%20companies%20have%20been%20pulling%20out%20their%20operations%20en-masse%20from%20the%20state%20in%20response%20to%20pressure%20from%20investors%20and%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FT's%20survey%20of%20600%20firms'%20financial%20reports%20showed%20that%20176%20of%20these%20have%20faced%20balance-sheet%20losses%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20sale%2C%20closure%2C%20or%20reduction%20in%20Russian%20business.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20losses%20were%20concentrated%20in%20a%20few%20heavily-exposed%20sectors%20such%20as%20energy%20and%20utilities.%20Three%20companies%20%E2%80%93%20BP%2C%20Shell%20and%20TotalEnergies%20%E2%80%93%20faced%20penalties%20of%20%E2%82%AC40.6%20billion.%20But%20the%20losses%20were%20more%20than%20covered%20thanks%20to%20higher%20energy%20prices%20which%20delivered%20bumper%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20energy%20and%20utilities%20were%20excluded%20from%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20largest%20writedowns%20come%20from%20Germany's%20chemical%20and%20automotive%20industries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20companies%20decided%20to%20cut%20ties.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yalerussianbusinessretreat.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20ongoing%20Yale%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20just%20over%20half%20of%20the%201%2C000%20companies%20that%20pledged%20to%20leave%20Russia%20have%20managed%20to%20make%20a%20clean%20break%20with%20the%20country.%20The%20tracker%20was%20last%20updated%20August%207.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20a%20company%20lost%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20leaving%20Russia%2C%20those%20who%20stay%20risk%20much%20bigger%20losses%2C%26quot%3B%20Nabi%20Abdullaev%2C%20partner%20at%20strategic%20consultancy%20Control%20Risks%2C%20told%20the%20FT.%20%26quot%3BIt%20turns%20out%20that%20cut%20and%20run%20was%20the%20best%20strategy%20for%20companies%20deciding%20what%20to%20do%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war.%20The%20faster%20you%20left%2C%20the%20lower%20your%20loss.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-seize-danone-carlsberg-kremlin-friendly-businessmen-interest-vladimir-putin-2023-7%5C%22%3EAfter%20the%20Kremlin's%20seizure%20of%20Danone%20and%20Carlsberg's%20assets%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20experts%20fear%20that%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20could%20make%20it%20even%20more%20difficult%20for%20companies%20to%20exit%20Russia.%20The%20state%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-kremlin-putin-priority-rights-shares-exiting-foreign-companies-seize-2023-7%5C%22%3Eapproving%20a%20new%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20puts%20the%20Kremlin%20first%20in%20line%20to%20seize%20the%20shares%20of%20strategic%20companies%20whose%20shareholders%20exit%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20law%20may%20add%20to%20the%20increasi