C%20thanks%20to%20oil%20supply%20cuts%20by%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Russia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ztayeb%40businessinsider.com%20(Zahra%20Tayeb)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fus-gas-prices-oil-inflation-smile-mohamed-el-erian-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20rejects%20Go%20First%20plea%20against%20Delhi%20HC%20nod%20to%20lessors%20to%20access%20planes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691397644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-05%2F04%2Ffull%2F1683222810-491.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20August%203%2C%20the%20airline%20had%20moved%20to%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Delhi%20HC's%20order%20to%20allow%20lessors%20to%20inspect%20the%20aircraft%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fsc-rejects-go-first-plea-against-delhi-hc-nod-to-lessors-to-access-planes-123080700323_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Could%20Have%20Adverse%20Impact%20on%20Press%20Freedom%2C%20Say%20Editors%20Guild%20and%20DIGIPUB%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F06140651%2FIMG_6391-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%20and%20DIGIPUB%20expressed%20a%20series%20of%20concerns%20they%20have%20over%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20saying%20it%20carries%20various%20provisions%20that%20can%20have%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20press%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20published%20on%20August%206%2C%20the%20EGI%20said%20the%20Bill%20could%20be%20used%20to%20widen%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20existing%20powers%20of%20censorship%20because%20Clause%2037(1)(b)%20will%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccensor%20content%20on%20vague%20and%20unspecified%20grounds%20%E2%80%98in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20general%20public'%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20exemptions%20for%20journalists%20from%20certain%20obligations%20of%20the%20law%2C%20where%20the%20reporting%20on%20certain%20entities%20in%20public%20interest%20may%20conflict%20with%20their%20right%20to%20personal%20data%20protection.%20The%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20report%20had%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%98If%20journalists%20were%20made%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20grounds%20of%20processing%20personal%20data%2C%20it%20would%20be%20extremely%20onerous%20for%20them%20to%20access%20information%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%98mandating%20grounds%20of%20processing%20like%20consent%20would%20mean%20that%20accounts%20that%20are%20unfavourable%20to%20the%20data%20principal%20would%20simply%20not%20get%20published%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EGI%20also%20raised%20concerns%20that%20the%20Bull%20could%20%E2%80%9Cunreasonably%20widen%20the%20scope%20of%20exemptions%E2%80%9D%20available%20to%20public%20information%20officers%20of%20government%20ministries%20and%20departments%20to%20reject%20RTI%20applications%20on%20the%20simple%20basis%20that%20the%20information%20sought%20%E2%80%98relates%20to%20personal%20information%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20exemptions%20provided%20to%20the%20government%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20are%20near-absolute%2C%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20%5BDPB%5D%20to%20be%20constituted%20thereunder%20has%20not%20been%20provided%20sufficient%20independence%20and%20rulemaking%20powers%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20adds%2C%20noting%20that%20because%20that%20all%20members%20of%20the%20DPB%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20its%20%E2%80%9Cindependence%20remains%20in%20doubt%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDIGIPUB%2C%20a%20foundation%20formed%20by%20digital-only%20news%20organisations%2C%20echoed%20similar%20concerns%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20proposed%20requirement%20for%20children%20to%20have%20parental%20consent%20for%20access%20to%20online%20news%20publications%2C%20especially%20for%20children%20from%20the%20ages%2013%20to%2017.%20DIGIPUB%20said%20that%20this%20will%20%E2%80%9Cgreatly%20restrict%20their%20access%20to%20legitimate%20news%20sources%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAdditionally%2C%20the%20requirement%20preventing%20Data%20Fiduciaries%20from%20processing%20the%20data%20of%20children%20will%20mean%20that%20merely%20in%20order%20to%20access%20news%2C%20they%20will%20have%20to%20register%2Flogin.%20The%20approach%20towards%20protection%20of%20Children%20online%20needs%20to%20be%20reconsidered%2C%20in%20order%20to%20not%20hamper%20their%20access%20to%20knowledge%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20statements%20issued%20by%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20DIGIPUB%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20has%20been%20presented%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20August%203%2C%202023%20by%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Union%20Minister%20for%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%2C%20Mr.%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw.%20The%20bill%20carries%20various%20provisions%3Cbr%3E%5Cnthat%20can%20have%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20press%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20highlight%20some%20of%20the%20primary%20concerns%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EA.%20Concerns%20over%20democratic%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20note%20the%20irregularities%20in%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20brought%20before%20the%20Parliament.%20Bypassing%20democratic%20processes%2C%20such%20as%20transparency%20in%20the%20public%20consultation%20process%20as%20well%20as%20lapses%20in%20parliamentary%20procedure%20in%20tabling%20the%20Bill%20before%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%2C%20have%20contributed%20to%20the%20drafting%20of%20a%20Bill%20that%20provides%20significantly%20lower%20protections%20than%20those%20envisaged%20initially%20by%20the%20Justice%20BN%20Srikrishna%20Expert%20Committee%20and%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20landmark%20Privacy%20Judgment%20of%20Justice%20K.S.%20Puttaswamy%20v.%20Union%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EB.%20Concerns%20over%20surveillance%20over%20censorship%20and%20lack%20of%20surveillance%20reform%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20note%2C%20with%20dismay%2C%20that%20while%20the%20Bill%2C%20ostensibly%20to%20promote%20data%20protection%2C%20has%20failed%20to%20make%20any%20provisions%20that%20bring%20about%20the%20surveillance%20reform%20that%20is%20urgently%20needed%2C%20and%20in%20fact%20creates%20an%20enabling%20framework%20for%20surveillance%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources.%20While%20clause%2017(2)(a)%20allows%20the%20Union%20Government%20to%20issue%20a%20notification%20exempting%20any%20%E2%80%9Cinstrumentality%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20Bill%2C%20thereby%20out%20of%20the%20ambit%20of%20data%20protection%20restrictions%2C%20including%20internal%20sharing%20and%20processing%20of%20data%2C%20Section%2017(4)%20allows%20the%20government%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20to%20retain%20personal%20data%20for%20an%20unlimited%20period%20of%20time.%20Additionally%2C%20under%20Section%2036%2C%20the%20Government%20can%20ask%20any%20public%20or%20private%20entity%20(Data%20Fiduciary)%20to%20furnish%20personal%20information%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EC.%20Concerns%20over%20widening%20of%20censorship%20powers%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Bill%20provides%20the%20Union%20Government%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20widen%20its%20existing%20powers%20of%20censorship.%20Clause%2037(1)(b)%20of%20the%20Bill%20will%20allow%20the%20Union%20Government%20to%20censor%20content%20on%20vague%20and%20unspecified%20grounds%20%E2%80%98in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20general%20public%E2%80%99.%20This%20will%20increase%20censorship%20powers%20well%20beyond%20what%20is%20presently%20provided%20for%20under%20Section%2069A%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%2C%20and%20may%20even%20be%20unconstitutional%20for%20going%20beyond%20the%20reasonable%20restrictions%20on%20free%20expression%20enumerated%20under%20Article%2019(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ED.%20Concerns%20over%20lack%20of%20exemptions%20for%20journalistic%20activities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20exemptions%20for%20journalists%20from%20certain%20obligations%20of%20the%20law%2C%20where%20the%20reporting%20on%20certain%20entities%20in%20public%20interest%20may%20conflict%20with%20their%20right%20to%20personal%20data%20protection.%20The%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20report%20had%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9CIf%20journalists%20were%20made%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20grounds%20of%20processing%20personal%20data%2C%20it%20would%20be%20extremely%20onerous%20for%20them%20to%20access%20information%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmandating%20grounds%20of%20processing%20like%20consent%20would%20mean%20that%20accounts%20that%20are%20unfavourable%20to%20the%20data%20principal%20would%20simply%20not%20get%20published.%E2%80%9D%20It%20had%20thus%20provided%20a%20framework%20for%20balance%20between%20personal%20data%20protection%20and%20public%20interest%2C%20which%20we%20note%20is%20missing%20from%20the%20current%20bill.%20This%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20journalistic%20activity%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EE.%20Concern%20over%20impact%20on%20the%20Right%20To%20Information%20(RTI)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20has%20been%20already%20been%20pointed%20out%20by%20some%20activists%2C%20certain%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20Clause%2044(3)%20for%20instance%2C%20unreasonably%20widen%20the%20scope%20of%20exemptions%20available%20to%20Public%20Information%20Officers%20of%20government%20ministries%20and%20departments%20to%20reject%20RTI%20applications%20under%20Section%208(1)(i)%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%2C%20on%20the%20simple%20basis%20that%20the%20information%20sought%20%E2%80%98relates%20to%20personal%20information%E2%80%99.%20The%20RTI%20Act%20in%20its%20present%20form%20strikes%20a%20balance%20between%20privacy%20and%20the%20right%20to%20public%20information.%20This%20provision%20shifts%20the%20balance%20in%20favour%20of%20non-disclosure%20of%20information%2C%20including%20information%20which%20is%20being%20sought%20by%20journalists%20in%20public%20interest%2C%20thereby%20reducing%20accountability.%20It%20is%20necessary%20that%20the%20RTI%20Act%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3Enot%20be%20weakened.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3EF.%20Concerns%20over%20the%20composition%20of%20and%20appointment%20to%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhile%20exemptions%20provided%20to%20the%20government%20and%20its%20instrumentalities%20are%20near-absolute%2C%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20to%20be%20constituted%20thereunder%20has%20not%20been%20provided%20sufficient%20independence%20and%20rulemaking%20powers.%20Lawyers%2C%20scholars%20and%20even%20judgments%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20have%20noted%20that%20Tribunals%20(such%20as%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board)%20must%20remain%20independent%20of%20control%20by%20the%20executive%2C%20to%20maintain%20their%20effectiveness%20and%20credibility.%20However%2C%20given%20that%20all%20members%20of%20the%20DPB%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20Union%20Government%20(Clause%2019(2))%2C%20its%20independence%20remains%20in%20doubt.%20Considering%20the%20huge%20fines%20that%20can%20potentially%20be%20imposed%2C%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Board%20from%20executive%20interference%20is%20vital%20to%20preserve%20liberty.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Guild%20urges%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20to%20reconsider%20the%20provisions%20that%20Editor%E2%80%99s%20Guild%20of%20India%20has%20highlighted%2C%20and%20work%20to%20offer%20a%20data%20protection%20legislation%20to%20Indian%20citizens%20that%20does%20not%20compromise%20their%20right%20to%20free%20expression%2C%20right%20to%20information%20and%20right%20to%20a%20free%20press.%20Further%2C%20the%20Guild%20urges%20the%20Speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20to%20place%20the%20Bill%20before%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20for%20deliberation%20on%20the%20issues%20raised%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20reconsider%20those%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Guild%20has%20already%20written%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20leaders%20of%20political%20parties%20in%20both%20the%20houses%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Minister%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%2C%20highlighting%20our%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDIGIPUB%20is%20concerned%20about%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20August%203%2C%202023%2C%20as%20its%20provisions%20could%20potentially%20impinge%20on%20citizens%E2%80%99%20and%20journalists%E2%80%99%20rights%20to%20privacy%2C%20information%2C%20and%20freedom%20of%20expression.%20The%20passing%20of%20this%20Bill%20in%20the%20current%20form%20will%20greatly%20undermine%20press%20freedom%2C%20and%20Digipub%20echoes%20the%20concerns%20raised%20by%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%2C%20alongwith%20highlighting%20some%20additional%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECensorship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClause%2012(3)%20enables%20a%20person%20who%20consented%20to%20share%20personal%20data%20with%20a%20news%20publication%2Fjournalist%20to%20exercise%20right%20to%20erasure%2C%20and%20have%20personal%20information%20and%2For%20the%20news%20article%20removed%20even%20if%20public%20interest%20is%20greater.%20More%20often%20than%20not%2C%20those%20who%20want%20to%20be%20forgotten%20are%20the%20ones%20who%20need%20to%20be%20remembered.%20The%20Bill%20needs%20to%20ensure%20that%20this%20clause%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20become%20a%20mechanism%20for%20censorship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Clause%2037(1)(b)%20also%20allows%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20censor%20information%20without%20any%20clearly%20specified%20grounds.%20This%20gives%20the%20government%20censorship%20powers%20beyond%20the%20existing%20provisions%20under%20Section%2069A%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%20which%20itself%20operates%20without%20any%20transparency%20and%20public%20accountability%2C%20thereby%20restricting%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20is%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20freedom%20of%20the%20press.%20This%20censorship%20clause%20has%20no%20place%20in%20a%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExemptions%20for%20publicly%20available%20data%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%2C%20via%20Clause%203(c)(ii)%20exempts%20publicly%20available%20personal%20data%20from%20its%20provisions%20of%20the%20bill.%20This%20means%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20surveillance%2Fprofiling%20companies%20can%20use%20automated%20tools%20to%20scrape%20and%20profile%20data%20of%20every%20Indian%20citizen%20from%20their%20social%20media%20profiles%2C%20as%20well%20as%20from%20news%20publications%2C%20without%20their%20consent.%20This%20is%20particularly%20worrying%20when%20you%20consider%20the%20rapid%20deployment%20of%20CCTVs%20in%20the%20country%2C%20along%20with%20the%20increasing%20sophistication%20of%20facial%20recognition%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20exemption%20not%20only%20enables%20the%20usage%20of%20automated%20tools%20to%20profile%20citizens%2C%20including%20journalists%2C%20it%20also%20potentially%20enables%20the%20scraping%20of%20content%20of%20media%20publications%20and%20reports%20about%20individuals%2C%20which%20amounts%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20copyright.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20scraping%20tools%20are%20commonly%20used%20in%20Data%20Journalism%2C%20in%20public%20interest.%20Given%20that%20we%20are%20in%20an%20environment%20of%20rapid%20acceleration%20of%20AI%20development%2C%20we%20would%20urge%20that%20any%20such%20clauses%20need%20careful%20consideration%20of%20their%20impact%20on%20privacy%2C%20fair%20use%20and%20copyright.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESurveillance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20there%20is%20a%20compelling%20need%20for%20surveillance%20reform%20in%20India%2C%20the%20Bill%20can%20lead%20to%20significantly%20hampering%20journalistic%20activities%20in%20the%20country%20by%20enabling%20surveillance%20of%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources.%20At%20present%2C%20surveillance%20systems%20like%20the%20Centralised%20Monitoring%20System%20enable%20the%20Indian%20government%20surveillance%20of%20phone%20calls%20and%20messages.%20The%20Bill%20allows%20the%20government%20to%20exempt%20any%20%E2%80%9Cinstrumentality%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20as%20per%20Clause%2017(2)(a)%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20share%20and%20process%20personal%20data%20without%20transparency%20or%20accountability.%20Section%2017(4)%20makes%20exemptions%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20its%20%E2%80%98instrumentalities%E2%80%99%20to%20retain%20personal%20data%20for%20longer%20periods%20of%20time%2C%20even%20when%20the%20individual%20has%20withdrawn%20their%20consent%20or%20demanded%20to%20erase%20their%20data.%20Section%2036%20also%20empowers%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20call%20for%20information%20from%20any%20data%20processing%20private%20entity%2C%20thereby%20converting%20every%20private%20company%20into%20an%20instrument%20of%20surveillance%2C%20thus%20compromising%20not%20just%20the%20privacy%20of%20journalists%20and%20their%20sources%2C%20but%20the%20privacy%20of%20all%20citizens%20of%20India.%20This%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20safeguards%20provided%20to%20citizens%20under%20the%20Puttaswamy%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20judgment%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%20and%20the%20Bill%20needs%20to%20be%20amended%20to%20include%20clauses%20for%20surveillance%20reform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELack%20of%20exemptions%20for%20journalists%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20times%2C%20journalism%20about%20individuals%20is%20at%20odds%20with%20their%20need%20for%20personal%20data%20protection%2C%20and%20information%20sought%20to%20be%20kept%20private%20needs%20to%20be%20made%20public%2C%20in%20public%20interest.%20An%20earlier%20version%20of%20the%20Bill%20drafted%20by%20the%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20took%20this%20into%20account%20while%20recommending%20exemptions%20for%20journalists%2C%20saying%20that%20said%20that%20journalists%20would%20find%20it%20very%20difficult%20to%20access%20information%20if%20they%20had%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20legislation%2C%20and%20that%20making%20consent%20always%20mandatory%20for%20the%20processing%20of%20personal%20information%20would%20mean%20that%20information%20unfavourable%20to%20certain%20individuals%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20simply%20not%20get%20published.%E2%80%9D%20The%20current%20version%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20however%2C%20makes%20no%20exceptions%20for%20public%20interest%20journalism%2C%20and%20as%20such%2C%20opens%20up%20media%20organisations%20to%20legal%20risks%20when%20they%20report%20on%20activities%20of%20certain%20individuals.%20This%20will%20hamper%20journalistic%20activity%20and%20greatly%20weaken%20the%20fourth%20estate.%20We%20urge%20the%20government%20to%20consider%20creating%20exemptions%20for%20journalists%20in%20public%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImpact%20on%20right%20to%20information%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20has%20been%20a%20critical%20tool%20for%20journalists%20to%20hold%20the%20government%20to%20account%20in%20public%20interest.%20Clause%2044(3)%20widens%20the%20scope%20of%20exemptions%20given%20to%20Public%20Information%20Officers%20in%20the%20government%20to%20reject%20requests%20for%20information%2C%20by%20substituting%20Clause%208(1)(j)%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act.%20This%20provision%20weakens%20the%20RTI%20Act%20since%20it%20allows%20Public%20Information%20Officers%20to%20reject%20RTI%20applications%20if%20the%20information%20pertains%20to%20the%20personal%20information.%20We%E2%80%99re%20already%20seeing%20RTI%20requests%20from%20journalists%20being%20rejected%20on%20frivolous%20grounds%2C%20and%20being%20overturned%20only%20on%20appeals.%20This%20change%20will%20significantly%20hinder%20the%20ability%20of%20journalists%20to%20seek%20information%20of%20importance%20to%20reporting%20in%20public%20interest%2C%20and%20should%20be%20deleted%20from%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAccess%20to%20news%20by%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildren%20today%20are%20digital%20natives%2C%20and%20their%20access%20to%20information%20is%20essentially%20online.%20We%E2%80%99re%20concerned%20that%20the%20requirement%20of%20parental%20consent%20for%20access%20to%20online%20news%20publications%2C%20especially%20for%20Children%20from%20the%20ages%2013%20to%2017%2C%20when%20they%E2%80%99re%20beginning%20to%20form%20their%20world%20view%2C%20will%20greatly%20restrict%20their%20access%20to%20legitimate%20news%20sources.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20requirement%20preventing%20Data%20Fiduciaries%20from%20processing%20the%20data%20of%20children%20will%20mean%20that%20merely%20in%20order%20to%20access%20news%2C%20they%20will%20have%20to%20register%2Flogin.%20The%20approach%20towards%20protection%20of%20Children%20online%20needs%20to%20be%20reconsidered%2C%20in%20order%20to%20not%20hamper%20their%20access%20to%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EComposition%20and%20lack%20of%20rulemaking%20powers%20of%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20independence%20is%20in%20question%2C%20as%20the%20Union%20government%20holds%20the%20power%20to%20appoint%20the%20Board%E2%80%99s%20members.%20The%20Board%20can%20inquire%20into%20complaints%20of%20breaches%20and%20impose%20huge%20financial%20penalties.%20A%20parliamentary%20panel%20had%20earlier%20recommended%20that%20a%20selection%20committee%20should%20nominate%20the%20members%20of%20an%20independent%20Data%20Protection%20Authority%2C%20which%20would%20ensure%20the%20body%20is%20credible%20and%20free%20from%20any%20influence.%20In%20addition%2C%20in%20order%20to%20safeguard%20the%20privacy%20of%20individuals%2C%20it%20is%20important%20that%20the%20Board%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20rules%20and%20regulations%20in%20response%20to%20privacy%20concerns%20in%20an%20evolving%20digital%20domain%2C%20and%20also%20hold%20the%20government%20to%20account.%20A%20Bill%20is%20as%20effective%20as%20its%20enforcement%2C%20and%20the%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%20will%20be%20ineffective%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20empowered%20Data%20Protection%20Authority.%20The%20construct%2C%20role%20and%20powers%20of%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Board%20need%20to%20be%20reconsidered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDIGIPUB%20urges%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20to%20review%20the%20concerns%20highlighted%20by%20us%20and%20other%20organisations%20and%20activists%2C%20and%20have%20a%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20reconsider%20the%20Bill%20and%20formulate%20a%20legislation%20that%20does%20not%20encroach%20on%20peoples%E2%80%99%20rights.%20Furthermore%2C%20we%20request%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20to%20take%20the%20issues%20raised%20by%20DIGIPUB%20into%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20DIGIPUB%E2%80%99s%20statement%20was%20added%20to%20this%20article%20after%20it%20was%20published.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691396956000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F06140651%2FIMG_6391-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-bill-adverse-impact-press-freedom-editors-guild%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20media%20organisations%20pointed%20out%20several%20concerns%20they%20have%20over%20certain%20provisions%20in%20the%20Bill%2C%20including%20the%20possibility%20of%20wider%20censorship%20and%20surveillance%20powers%20and%20reducing%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-bill-adverse-i