%3EThe%20Bill%2C%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20existing%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPress%20and%20Registration%20of%20Books%20Act%2C%201867%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(PRB)%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Frajya-sabha-passes-press-and-registration-of-periodicals-bill%2Farticleshow%2F102395359.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Epassed%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20by%20a%20voice%20vote%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday%20(August%203)%20in%20the%20Opposition%E2%80%99s%20absence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20press%20release%2C%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20said%20that%20the%20new%20legislation%20%E2%80%9Cwidens%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20state%20to%20have%20more%20intrusive%20and%20arbitrary%20checks%E2%80%9D%20in%20how%20a%20publication%20functions%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20of%20the%20provisions%20were%20%E2%80%9Cvague%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20ambiguity%20could%20have%20%E2%80%9Cadverse%20implications%20on%20press%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20said%20that%20the%20new%20Bill%20allows%20government%20agencies%20other%20than%20the%20press%20registrar%20to%20conduct%20its%20functions%2C%20which%20could%20even%20include%20police%20and%20other%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%2C%20and%20called%20the%20move%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20distressing%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20journalists%E2%80%99%20body%20pointed%20out%20that%20Sections%204(1)%20and%2011(4)%20of%20the%20Bill%20allow%20the%20government%20to%20deny%20the%20right%20to%20bring%20out%20a%20periodical%2C%20to%20persons%20convicted%20of%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%20act%20or%20unlawful%20activity%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20having%20done%20anything%20against%20the%20security%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20the%20liberal%20and%20arbitrary%20use%20of%20UAPA%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20criminal%20laws%2C%20including%20Sedition%2C%20against%20journalists%20and%20media%20organisations%20to%20suppress%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20the%20Guild%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20by%20the%20introduction%20of%20these%20new%20provisions%2C%20and%20the%20way%20they%20can%20be%20misused%20to%20deny%20the%20right%20to%20bring%20out%20news%20publications%20to%20persons%20who%20are%20critical%20of%20governments%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20criticised%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20enter%20premises%20of%20news%20organisations%2C%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%9Cexcessively%20intrusive%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%2019%20of%20the%20Bill%20gives%20the%20Union%20government%20powers%20to%20frame%20rules%20under%20which%20news%20publishing%20is%20to%20be%20done%20in%20India.%20The%20statement%20cited%20the%20example%20of%20IT%20Rules%202021%2C%20and%20the%20latest%20amendments%20made%20to%20it%20regarding%20%E2%80%9Csetting%20up%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98fact%20checking%20unit%E2%80%99%20with%20sweeping%20powers%20to%20order%20content%20take%20down%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20that%20such%20rules%20be%20clearly%20defined%20in%20the%20act%20and%20not%20be%20left%20to%20the%20discretion%20of%20a%20future%20government%20or%20authority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Guild%20said%20that%20emphasis%20of%20the%20registrar%20and%20the%20Bill%20should%20remain%20on%20%E2%80%98registration%E2%80%99%20and%20not%20%E2%80%98regulation%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20could%20potentially%20restrict%20press%20freedom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20was%20signed%20by%20president%20Seema%20Mustafa%2C%20general%20secretary%20Anant%20Nath%2C%20and%20treasurer%20Shriram%20Pawar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E