%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Our%20work%20will%20never%20stop%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECollaboration%20rather%20than%20confrontation%20has%20been%20PHRA%E2%80%99s%20policy%20all%20along%2C%20and%20has%20helped%20them%20succeed%20in%20their%20endeavours.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20officials%20see%20our%20enthusiasm%20and%20realise%2C%20we%20will%20not%20take%20no%20for%20an%20answer%2C%20they%20start%20helping.%20And%20when%20they%20see%20the%20good%20work%20we%20are%20doing%2C%20they%20respond%20positively%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Dr%20Shukla.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssistant%20Municipal%20Commissioner%20Vinayak%20Vispute%2C%20H%20west%20ward%2C%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CPHRA%20is%20doing%20good%20work%20and%20the%20biogas%20plant%20is%20an%20innovative%20project%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20work%20under%20our%20care.%20They%20also%20support%20us%20in%20many%20of%20our%20initiatives.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20pandemic%20has%20posed%20a%20challenge%20for%20PHRA%20in%20terms%20of%20slackening%20of%20waste%20segregation%2C%20the%20association%20is%20trying%20to%20bring%20things%20back%20on%20track%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year.%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20COVID%20our%20segregation%20slowed%20down%20and%20now%20it%20is%20between%2055%20and%2060%25.%20We%20are%20trying%20to%20raise%20it%20and%20achieve%20zero%20garbage%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year.%20Our%20future%20plans%20include%20setting%20up%20a%20seven-ton%20biogas%20plant%20to%20convert%20wet%20waste%20to%20CNG%20and%20enable%20all%20civic%2F%20police%20vehicles%20in%20our%20ward%20to%20run%20on%20CNG%2C%20free%20of%20cost.%20Our%20work%20will%20never%20stop.%20There%20will%20always%20be%20something%20to%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20avers%20Madhu.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWritten%20by%20Janaki%20Krishnamoorthi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690894724000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2Fpali-hill-1690870702.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D325858%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Pali%20Hill%20Residents%E2%80%99s%20Association%20began%20with%20eight%20women%20in%20the%2090s%20who%20dreamt%20of%20transforming%20their%20neighbourhood%20into%20a%20cleaner%2C%20greener%2C%20and%20safer%20home.%20The%20members%20recall%20how%20they%20achieved%20this%20award-winning%20transformation%20over%20two%20decades.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Guest%20Contributor%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Were%20Farmers%20Throwing%20Out%20Tomatoes%3F%20Engineer%E2%80%99s%20Solar%20Dryers%20Help%20Farmers%20Earn%20in%20Dire%20Times%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEarly%20this%20year%20when%20farmers%20in%20the%20region%20were%20selling%20tomatoes%20at%20a%20throwaway%20price%2C%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20Nitin%20Ramesh%20Dhingre%20took%20a%20smart%20decision.%20He%20converted%20the%20fresh%20produce%20into%20dried%20products%20using%20a%20solar%20dryer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20enough%20supply%20in%20the%20market%2C%20prices%20reduce.%20Earlier%2C%20we%20were%20selling%20tomatoes%20for%20Rs%2050%20per%20crate%20of%2020%20kilos%2C%20which%20comes%20to%20Rs%202.5%20for%201%20kg.%20We%20were%20unable%20to%20even%20get%20its%20cost%20of%20production.%20Additionally%2C%20we%20have%20to%20spend%20on%20harvesting%20the%20crop%20and%20transporting%20it%20to%20the%20market%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%2038-year-old%20farmer%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20last%20December%2C%20I%20started%20drying%20the%20excess%20produce.%20For%20the%20same%20quantity%2C%20for%20which%20I%20would%20get%20Rs%2050%2C%20now%20I%20earn%20Rs%20350%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Nitin%2C%20who%20grows%20tomatoes%2C%20grapes%2C%20and%20onions%20on%20a%20five-acre%20land%20in%20his%20village%20Matur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5